                                          CSS POSITION

static(default);we cant add offsets(top,bottom,left right)

relative:In this it will move with respect to its static position(top,bottom,left,right);
         Firstly in css make position:relative then use top, bottom,left or right

absolute: if we have parent, it takes the absolute position below the parent,and can even overlap.It takes 
position with respect to the parent
         (top,...);

fixed:It position elements according to viewport of different devices() like in nav bars un some websites

Sticky:- position on basis of users scroll position,similar to fixed,but becomes fixed when end is touched by 
scroll bar

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                          CSS DISPLAY
It is used to control the layout,we can also put none

1.block:-div,para,heading tags(h1,...)etc
2.inline:-span,img
If we make a block element inline we cannot change its height or width,but if we make it inline block,we can 
do it
3.inline-block:It allows both inline as well as block properties,like height and width
4.flex
5.grid
